snippet.textDisplay:
The song is composed by a Persian-speaking Ustad Zaland. Ustad Zaland is the father of Farid Zaland (Zoland) one of the best music composers in Iran. He has composed songs for several well-known and famous singers such as Hayedeh, Dariush, Googoosh, Abi and also his sister. He donated this song to an Iranian 1960s singer Googoosh).
1. First: 1960er https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yqrKkcbQuIo
2. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dfxyi47tM_c
3.  2017 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aj95b60WZEU

The song is sung in an Indian movie in 1988 by Lata ji's sister Asha Bhosle  "enemies of love".
Song.: Dil Khoya Khoya Gum Sum
 Singer: Asha Bhosle
 Lyrics: . Anjaan,Prakash Mehra
 Movie:.Mohabbat Ke Dushman 1988
 Music...Anandji,Kalyanji,
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CoEV9vxjg-U

Original music : Ustad Zaland Persian Singer from Afghansitan : sicnce 1964 is Persian  Dari 

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dari_language
http://afghanistandl.nyu.edu/search/?q=Farsi&sort=title.sort&start=0

Fact is Dari = Persian = Tajiki (I love Persian and Tajiki and Persian Dari Poetry) In Afghanistan, there are at least 14 languages written in the constitution. But Persian and Pashto are the official languages. Both languages are Indo-Iranian languages. (The Urbücher of the languages are Sanskrit, Regveda and Gathas of Zende Awesta) Pashtun = Afghans = Pathans =  Rolilla. 
Summary: 
The song is an Indo-Iranian and Central Asian song exactly as well as Spring Festival. Seven is a lucky number: like Detention Mewa, Haftsin and Spring Festival Bahar or Bihar or Nava Viharar. Also in India the couple orbits the hearth seven times.

snippet.textDisplay:
English translation  Man Amadeam or Man Amada am!
I've come, woe woe
I've come
that the love shouts out
I've come
that the coquetry makes a foundation
Refrain:
I've come
I've come
that the love shouts out
I've come
that the coquetry makes a foundation
I've come, woe

o my sweetheart, may you live for 100 years
o my sweetheart, may you live for 100 years
you sat at my side, may you be my neighbour
may you be my neighbour, so that your hand gives me shade
maybe you will be my destiny

Refrain:

love came and pitched a tent in the field of my heart
love came and pitched a tent in the field of my heart
love threw its faithful chain at my heart's feet
if love doesn't respond to the yells of my heart
oh my heart, woe
oh my heart, oh my heart

Refrain:

come so that we can leave here, me and you
come so that we can leave here, me and you
you take my hand and I will take your clothes
until a point where both of us fall ill
(we get sick) you because of the sorrow of loneliness, and I because of your sorrow
Refrain
